{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648490","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648490"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:54:27+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:54:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18314"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18314","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18314"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.03,0.93,0.02,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11032"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77463"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11032","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11032"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18314"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62975"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4944"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10955"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25600"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25605"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77463","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77463"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 58-year-old gentleman presents to the Emergency Department with a red, hot, swollen and painful right fourth toe which he describes as a sausage toe. He recalls possibly stepping on a thorn when he was gardening a week ago. He has Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus and hypertension. His last HbA1C was 7.5%.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following laboratory findings is most commonly associated with acute osteomyelitis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased haemoglobin level","Decreased white blood cell count","Elevated C-reactive protein","Normal erythrocyte sedimentation rate","Low platelet count"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAcute osteomyelitis is an infection of the bone that presents with fever, pain, and swelling over the affected area. It is associated with increased inflammatory markers in the blood.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn acute osteomyelitis, an \u003Cstrong\u003Eelevated C-reactive protein\u003C/strong\u003E is commonly observed. This is due to the inflammatory response triggered by the infection. Other inflammatory markers, such as the erythrocyte sedimentation rate, are also elevated.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased white blood cell count\u003C/strong\u003E - White blood cell count is usually elevated in response to infection\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal erythrocyte sedimentation rate\u003C/strong\u003E - This is elevated in acute osteomyelitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELow platelet count\u003C/strong\u003E - Platelet count is not usually affected in acute osteomyelitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased haemoglobin level\u003C/strong\u003E - Anaemia is not a common feature of acute osteomyelitis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute osteomyelitis is an infection of the bone that often leads to inflammation and increased levels of inflammatory markers.","Common laboratory findings in acute osteomyelitis include elevated erythrocyte sedimentation rate (ESR) and C-reactive protein (CRP).","Acute osteomyelitis can present with fever, pain, and swelling over the affected area."],"references":["Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Mohan, H. (2018). Textbook of pathology. Jaypee Brothers Medical Publishers.","Momodu II, Savaliya V. Osteomyelitis. [Updated 2023 May 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK532250/","Folpe, A., \u0026 Nielsen, G. P. (Eds.). (2022). Bone and Soft Tissue Pathology E-Book: A Volume in the Foundations in Diagnostic Pathology Series. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62975"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18314"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62975","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62975"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-07T08:33:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-07T08:34:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11032"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77463"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":